# @orbit/runtime

The generic async execution engine for Orbit. Implements the `Runtime`
responsibilities described in `docs/architecture.md`: tasks, a queue, a
worker pool, and an event bus.

This package contains **no AI, planner, memory, or tool logic**. It knows
how to create, queue, execute, and track tasks — it has no idea what a task
does. Future subsystems (tools, agents, planner) register handlers with a
`Runtime` instance via `register_handler(name, handler)`; this package never
imports from them.

## Install (editable, local development)

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

## Usage

```python
from orbit_runtime import Runtime

runtime = Runtime(num_workers=2)
await runtime.start()

async def greet(task):
    return f"hello, {task.payload['name']}"

runtime.register_handler("greet", greet)
task = await runtime.submit("greet", {"name": "orbit"})

runtime.get(task.id)          # inspect status/result as it progresses
runtime.list()                 # list all tasks
await runtime.cancel(task.id)  # cancel (cooperative if already running)

await runtime.stop()
```

See `docs/architecture.md` for how this fits into the rest of the system,
and `apps/api/src/orbit_api/core/runtime.py` for how `orbit-api` wires a
process-wide instance.
